This paper discusses the relationship between two models of contracts, binary session types and event structures, which are both topics in theoretical computer science. The paper also uses game-theoretic notions, which falls under the category of cs.GT. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
